To fix the code quality issue of having `console.log` statements in production code, you should remove or comment out the `console.log` statements before deploying the code to a production environment. 

Here's an example of how you can remove the `console.log` statement from the file src\app\api\ai\revolution\route.ts:

Before:
```typescript
console.log("Processing revolution request...");
```

After:
```typescript
// console.log("Processing revolution request...");
```

Make sure to review the rest of the code in the file and remove any other `console.log` statements that may be present before deploying to production.